{"type":"article","slug":"mic/content/27/1/11","journal":"mic","canonical":"https://www.sgmjournals.org/mic/content/27/1/11","meta":{"title":"Biological Assay of Cephalosporin C","authors":["BOND, JILLIAN M.","BRIMBLECOMBE, R. W.","CODNER, R. C."],"journalTitle":"Journal of General Microbiology","journalAbbrev":"","volume":"27","issue":"1","firstpage":"11","lastpage":"","date":"01/01/1962","doi":"10.1099/00221287-27-1-11","issn":[],"pmid":"13870924","mjid":"mic;27/1/11","section":"","abstractUrl":"http://mic.sgmjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/27/1/11","fulltextUrl":"","pdfUrl":"http://mic.sgmjournals.org/cgi/reprint/27/1/11.pdf","publicUrl":""},"abstractHtml":"<p>SUMMARY: A method of assaying the antibiotic cephalosporin C in low concentration in culture fluids by using a strain of <i>Vibrio cholerae</i> is described. The formation of spheroplasts of the test organism in subinhibitory concentrations of the antibiotic and chemically related compounds is discussed.</p>","bodyHtml":"","referencesHtml":"","affiliationsHtml":"","correspHtml":"","pdfPath":null,"summaryHtml":"","ccTier":"tier3-abstract","refdomains":0}